libbw64
------------------------------------------
The libbw64 library is a lightweight C++ header only library to read and write
BW64 files. BW64 is standardised as Recommendation ITU-R BS.2088 and the
successor of RF64.

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ebu/libbw64

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ebu/libbw64/archive/refs/tags/0.10.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbw64-0.10.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbw64-0.10.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbw64-0.10.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbw64-0.10.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbw64)
  /usr/include/bw64/bw64.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/chunks.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/parser.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/reader.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/utils.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/version.hpp
  /usr/include/bw64/writer.hpp
  /usr/share/cmake/libbw64/libbw64Config.cmake
  /usr/share/cmake/libbw64/libbw64ConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/share/cmake/libbw64/libbw64Targets.cmake
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbw64.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbw64/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libbw64/README.md

